Commentary.Commentary: Onto their batting now, Bangladesh really need to dig in. They wicket is a good one to bat on but they'll need to show a lot of application. South Africa on the other hand, will hope to build pressure by bowling the right lines and lengths and also hope the wicket wears off and they do get some assistance. Stay tuned for the reply.

For Bangladesh, it was hard work on a placid wicket! Their bowlers hardly got any assistance. The thing they'll be disappointed with is the ease they let the visitors score. Taijul Islam though yet again impressed with a five-fer but for the others, it was an effort to forget.

End of a marathon batting effort from South Africa! They won the toss, elected to bat and the batters responded in emphatic fashion. Three batters scored tons. Tony, Stubbs and Mulder. There were fifties from David Bedingham and Senuran Muthusamy too and that's what helped them to pile up a massive score on the board.

SIX! Bang! Brings it up in style! Top knock. He gets a juicy half volley on middle. He just lifts it down the ground and it goes all the way. Raises his bat, takes his helmet off and soaks in the applause. Also, that's the end of the South African innings as they have DECLARED!

South Africa continue to pile on the misery! They have batted themselves into a position from where losing the game becomes quite difficult and now they have stepped on the gas too. Both Senuran Muthusamy and Wiaan Mulder are batting with intent, the question is, when will the declaration come? Bangladesh on the other hand, need to continue to try and take wickets. The wicket is still good to bat on and they'll be hoping for this Sputh African innings to end soon. We expect some more entertaining batting after the break.

Commentary.Commentary: We are back. The players are out in the middle. A big session awaits for both teams. Taijul Islam to bowl first.
...Day 2, Session 2..

The ball turned, gripped and stayed low on many occasions. Taijul Islam bowled well and got three wickets. He got the breakthroughs and also got the big wicket of Kyle Verreynne. Ryan Rickelton and Wiaan Mulder though have made sure they do not lose any more wickets and have started to build another partnership. The pitch has started to open up and South Africa have to be really careful in the next session. Can they build a big stand? Let's find out in the next session.

A tale of two halves for South Africa - In the first hour they bossed it. Tony de Zorzi and David Bedingham started Day 2 well and scored plenty of runs. Tony de Zorzi brought up his 150 while David Bedingham scored his third Test half century. However, right after the drinks break, Bangladesh brought spin from both ends and the duo, Taijul Islam and Mehidy Hasan got plenty of purchases off the deck.
THREE! Shorter and outside off, Wiaan Mulder punches it to deep cover. The fielder chases and dives in the deep to save a single. That will be LUNCH.

Hello and welcome to the action of Day 2 between Bangladesh and South Africa. It was a run feast on Day 1 as the Proteas after winning the toss posted a massive total thanks to the double century partnership between Stubbs and De Zorzi. The latter was main stay right from the start. He got used to the pitch and later comfortably scored a brilliant century. Still unbeaten, he was well supported by Stubbs alongside who scored a century as well. Bangladesh on the other hand had to toil hard and are expected to ball all day again as South Africa have 8 wickets in hand. The pitch has started to open up and we could see the spinners get more purchase. Can Bangladesh create pressure in the first session? Let’s find out. Stay tuned.
...Day 2, Session 1...

For the Bangladesh bowlers, it was hard work, there was not a lot of assistance from the surface as well but the bowling wasn't at its best too. There were far too many boundary balls and the hosts just couldn't build pressure as they let South Africa score freely. They'll need wickets in heaps on Day 2 or it will be difficult for them to get back into the game. Will we see the hosts fight back? We will find out. Join us on Day 2 for the coverage. Till then, goodbye and take care!

STUMPS IT IS THEN! A cracking day for South Africa! They are in a fine position in this game. All thanks to two men, Tony de Zorzi and Tristan Stubbs. After a decent opening stand, Mariam fell but then came the marathon partnership. The two added over 200 and both scored tons. Stubbs fell shortly after getting to his ton but Tony is closing in on a 150. David Bedingham has began solidly and he'll be looking to cash in on this surface. South Africa are on course for a big first innings score and that's what they'll be wanting to do.

The light meter is out and the umpires now have decided the light is not good enough to continue. The players make their way off the field! Also, that should be the end of Day 1. Still not confirmed but don't see the players coming out again.

Commentary.Commentary: We're back!
... DAY 1, SESSION 3 ...

The Bangladesh bowlers have had to toil hard! There's not a lot in the surface for them and all they can do for now is stay patient. They though would love to stem the run flow a little. That may just build pressure but the hosts will need to bowl better lines and lengths for that. Will we see them being more disciplined after the break? We will find out.

Another fine session for South Africa and they are well on their way to a big first innings score! Stubbs and Tony de Zorzi have batted brilliantly. Their partnership is nearing the 150-run mark. Tony has got to his ton whereas, Stubbs will be eyeing one. More of the same is what South Africa will want after the break.

Hasan Mahmud looked good with the ball in the hand. He got the ball to swing both ways but South Africa negotiated him well. Taijul Islam and Mehidy Hasan got the odd balls to turn but apart from that there was not much for the hosts. Bangladesh certainly knows they have to work hard on this pitch for breakthroughs. It won't come easy and the Proteas won't let it slip easily as well. South Africa on the other hand will hope Stubbs and Tony de Zorzi build a huge partnership and take control of the innings. Join us for the second session in a while.

That will be Lunch! A solid first session for South Africa as they have scored 109 runs by losing just one wicket. They opted to bat first and have done well so far. Aiden Markram and Tony de Zorzi started with a positive intent. They scored runs regularly and made Bangladesh work hard for the breakthrough. In the first hour only one chance was created, Hasan Mahmud bowled in the channel but Tony de Zorzi survived as the keeper dropped it to his left. Taijul Islam though chipped in with the big wicket of Markram but apart from that it was all South Africa.

Commentary.Commentary: We are all set. The players are out in the middle. Aiden Markram and Tony de Zorzi to open for South Africa. Hasan Mahmud to bowl first.

Najmul Hossain Shanto says they would have batted first aswell but still looks a pretty good wicket to ball. Tells the players have done well in practice sessions. Mentions a good start with the bat is very important and they need to make big runs for the team. Informs about the changes.

Aiden Markram says they are going to bat first as it is a good wicket and could turn in later stages. Adds the top six baters need to put up a big score. Shares five days of Test cricket is a long way. Informs about the team.

Bangladesh (Playing XI) - Shadman Islam, Mahmudul Hasan Joy, Najmul Hossain Shanto (C), Mominul Haque, Mushfiqur Rahim, Mahidul Islam Ankon (WK), Zakir Hasan, Mehidy Hasan, Nahid Rana, Hasan Mahmud, Taijul Islam.

South Africa (Playing XI) - Aiden Markram (C), Tony de Zorzi, Tristan Stubbs, David Bedingham, Ryan Rickelton, Senuran Muthusamy, Kyle Verreynne (WK), Wiaan Mulder, Keshav Maharaj, Dane Paterson, Kagiso Rabada.
TOSS - South Africa have won the toss and will BAT.

It is a must-win game for them if they are to avoid a series defeat. The chips are down and they need the experienced heads to show some character. They can take some positives out of the little fight they showed in the latter half of the Test but they’ll need a complete game if they are to level the series. South Africa on the other hand, would want to repeat their performance from the last game. Can they do so? We will find out. Toss and teams in a bit.

The atmosphere in the Bangladesh camp is not the best and the loss at home never helps, especially a big loss, it could well be morale deflating. Nothing but a win can bring joy to the hosts at the moment but they’ll need to be at their extreme best if they are to beat a rampant South African side who are firing on all cylinders.
Day 1, Session 1...

Commentary.Commentary: Back quickly! The players have taken their position. Kagiso Rabada to bowl first.
...THIRD INNINGS...

The ball is turning! It won't get any easy for Bangladesh who will have to face the heat once again. Will we see a result today itself or Bangladesh batters will show some promise for the second time asking? Let's find out.

So, South Africa quickly wrap things up after the break. Mominul Haque's wicket was crucial for them and Senuran Muthusamy got the big breakthrough before Keshav Maharaj got the final wicket. The highlight of Bangladesh's innings was the stand between Haque and Islam. Bangladesh were reeling at 48/8 before the duo joined hands and avoided Bangladesh a heavy first innings score. South Africa bossing at this point. Their bowlers are up to the mark. They have to do it again as South Africa have forced the follow on.
OUT! GONE! That is the end! Very full and outside off, Islam swings his bat but hits off the toe end of his bat back to Keshav Maharaj who takes it to his right. Bangladesh still trail by 416 runs.

What a partnership this is for Bangladesh! Out of nowhere they are back in the game thanks to the 89 run stand between Haque and Islam. They have revived the hopes of Bangladeshi fans by showing a lot of character. They were 48/8 at one stage. Yes, 48/8 but look at the score now. Haque is the main man for them right now. He is played a vital innings and needs to continue and also needs able support from Islam who has done well so far. South Africa on the other hand, started with a bang. Taking wickets after wicket and it felt like the innings will be over within the first hour but look a bit frustrated with this partnership. Now, this break could help them to find their rhythm back. They'll hope that the remaining two wickets come quickly for them. Stay tuned.
Short in length and on off, Haque gets on top of the bounce and taps it to point. LUNCH!

South Africa continue to dominate the Test as we move to the action on Day 3. The Proteas did a commendable job on Day 2 to get in the drivers seat in the game. Centuries from De Zorzi and Stubbs followed by maiden Test century from Mulder helped South Africa post a mammoth first innings total. Bangladesh in reply, had to play a small passage with the bat and it didn’t help them as their top four in a flash against prime South African bowlers. Bangladesh are already in trouble and honestly it will get worse for them from here on as the pitch has started to help the bowlers. Can Bangladesh fight back and post a wicketless session? Let’s find out. Stay tuned.
...Day 3, Session 1...

Earlier in the day, South Africa batted, batted and batted and put up a massive score on the board and then it was their bowlers who have ended their day just as they would have liked. More of the same is what they would want on day 3. Bangladesh on the other hand, will hope their batters can show some fight. An exciting day awaits. Until then, goodbye and take care!

Very delighted because they were being rolled over by the South African bowlers here! They did not have a lot of time to bat but have lost four wickets. Ra Ada it was to begin, Dane Paterson rhen joined in the action and Maharaj got one too.

The light meter is out again and this time the umpires feel, they'll need to walk off! That should be STUMPS! South Africa will not be pleased walking off, Bangladesh on the other hand, will be very delighted.

data.Series_Status: South Africa lead the 2 Test series 1-0

Commentary.Commentary: That's it from this game! South Africa end up as comfortable winners of this series. Markram is presented with the trophy and he celebrates with his team. We hope you enjoyed our coverage. Until next time, goodbye and take care!

Aiden Markram says he's proud of the boys! They did really well in conditions which is not familiar. Credits Rabada for the way he bowled. They got to take it session by session, Test match by Test match!

Kagiso Rabada, PLAYER OF THE SERIES, says he's happy he got to bat first on this wicket. Credits the batters for the way they played. Mentions everybody contributed and everyone is willing to put their hand up. Ends by saying he needs to keep working hard and he hopes to keep going.
Tony de Zorzi, MAN OF THE MATCH, says he's very happy to contribute to the team. He just wanted to bat normally. Adds he hopes to continue his good form and he's able to do well.

Najmul Hossain Shanto says South Africa played really well but they were quite poor. Stated there's a lot to improve and they need to be a lot more consistent with the ball. States they need to improve in a lot of ways. Credits the ways Mominul Haque played. Ends by saying the senior players need to take responsibility.

South Africa did enforce that and it took them just over a session to take the 10 wickets again. This time it was the two spinners. They took 9 between them and have given South Africa and brilliant series win.

After declaring, their bowlers ran through the Bangladesh batting line-up. It was Rabada who was at his best. At one stage, Bangladesh were 8 down for below 50 and had it not been for Mominul, they would not have crossed the 100-run mark. They did manage to do so but were far behind the mark they needed to avoid a follow-on.

Another outstanding performance from the visitors! They have battered the hosts in this game! It was all about them right from the word go! First, they put up massive score on the board. They had three batters scoring tons and two of them with half tons.

OUT! Taken! That's the end of the game! Tossed up around off. Rana pushes at it with hard hands. This goes off the splice and straight to silly point. Another five wicket haul for Maharaj. SOUTH AFRICA WIN BY AN INNINGS AND 273 RUNS!

Commentary.Commentary: ... DAY 3, SESSION 3 ...

Bangladesh on the other hand, will hope the batters coming in can show some fight and hang in there! Their first air will probably be to take it to Day 4. Can they do so, we will find out in the last session.

South Africans are all over Bangladesh here! They are in a position where they can finish the game today itself. First, they got rid of the two wickets early in the session and then enforced the follow on. Their bowlers were brilliant yet again, it was Dane Paterson eji started things off and then it was the two left arm spinners who got amongst the wickets. South Africa will want more of the same after the break.

OUT! STUMPED! What has Hasan done? That was the last ball of the session! Hasan dances down the track. He does not get to the pitch of it and looks to block it out. This one goes on with the arm. Beats the bat and the keeper does the rest.
